296
00:26:55,394 --> 00:26:57,544
- Really.
- Yeah, it just needs a little sun,

297
00:26:57,396 --> 00:27:00,547
and you get sun
through both windows.

298
00:27:00,399 --> 00:27:04,551
I hope you don't mind.
My daughter gave it to me.

299
00:27:04,403 --> 00:27:06,553
No, it's okay.

300
00:27:06,405 --> 00:27:09,556
Good.

301
00:27:09,408 --> 00:27:10,557
Don't let Crawford bug you.

302
00:27:10,409 --> 00:27:14,561
He's a little soft around the edges,
but he's a good cop.

303
00:27:14,413 --> 00:27:17,564
Oh, leave that there.
It's all right.

304
00:27:17,416 --> 00:27:21,568
A little ambiance.

305
00:27:24,423 --> 00:27:27,574
Can I ask you
a personal question?

306
00:27:27,426 --> 00:27:29,576
Depends on the question.

307
00:27:29,428 --> 00:27:33,580
There's a rumor goin' around
that before you were in the bureau,

308
00:27:33,432 --> 00:27:35,582
that you were some kind of priest
or something.

309
00:27:35,434 --> 00:27:39,586
I was a seminary student. I didn't
make it as far as the priesthood.

310
00:27:39,438 --> 00:27:42,589
Still, that is some kind
of makeover. What happened?

311
00:27:42,441 --> 00:27:45,592
Found another way
to fight him.

312
00:27:45,444 --> 00:27:49,596
- You ready?
- Yeah.

313
00:27:49,448 --> 00:27:51,598
Fight who?

314
00:27:51,450 --> 00:27:55,602
Gentlemen, ladies.

315
00:27:55,454 --> 00:27:59,606
Listen up, please.

316
00:27:59,458 --> 00:28:02,609
Most of you have met
Special Agent John Travis.

317
00:28:02,461 --> 00:28:04,611
For those who haven't,
he's on loan to us...

318
00:28:04,463 --> 00:28:07,614
from the FBI Behavioral Sciences
Division at Quantico.

319
00:28:07,466 --> 00:28:10,617
Agent Travis's area of expertise
is ritual homicide...

320
00:28:10,469 --> 00:28:13,620
and occult-related crime.

321
00:28:13,472 --> 00:28:16,623
He was instrumental in breaking
the Santeria case last summer.

322
00:28:16,475 --> 00:28:19,626
No offense, but didn't that
case just end in an acquittal?

323
00:28:19,478 --> 00:28:20,627
[ Laughter ]

324
00:28:20,479 --> 00:28:24,631
That's right.

325
00:28:24,483 --> 00:28:26,633
The problem with prosecuting
occult crime...

326
00:28:26,485 --> 00:28:30,637
is the judicial concept
of reasonable doubt.

327
00:28:30,489 --> 00:28:33,640
The motives can be so bizarre,
so far beyond reason,

328
00:28:33,492 --> 00:28:36,643
that they're hard
for a jury to accept.

329
00:28:36,495 --> 00:28:38,645
That means we have to work
twice as hard to get a conviction.

330
00:28:38,497 --> 00:28:41,648
But our perp could just be
some run-of-the-mill psycho...

331
00:28:41,500 --> 00:28:43,650
who gets his stuff
off the back of a comic book.

332
00:28:43,502 --> 00:28:44,651
Idon't thinkso.

333
00:28:44,503 --> 00:28:48,655
Whoever did this has a background
in classic occult mysticism.

334
00:28:49,508 --> 00:28:51,658
This symbol was used
in ceremonial sacrifice...

335
00:28:51,510 --> 00:28:54,661
as far back
as 16th century Europe.

336
00:28:54,513 --> 00:28:56,663
The tines on the trident
point left,

337
00:28:56,515 --> 00:29:00,667
signifying the left-hand path
of Satanists.

338
00:29:00,519 --> 00:29:02,669
It was a sign of a sect
of Luciferians...

339
00:29:02,521 --> 00:29:05,672
who took the fallen angel
mythology literally.

340
00:29:05,524 --> 00:29:07,674
Then you think
the perp's got motives...

341
00:29:07,526 --> 00:29:10,677
- besides thrill kills?
- Yes.

342
00:29:10,529 --> 00:29:13,680
The crimes were meant
to be against God, not men.

343
00:29:13,532 --> 00:29:17,684
But all I can give you
right now is a time frame.

344
00:29:17,536 --> 00:29:21,688
All of the victims' bodies
also had these symbols...

345
00:29:22,541 --> 00:29:24,691
branded on them--
Pascua Negra.

346
00:29:24,543 --> 00:29:28,695
The translation would be
''Black Easter.''

347
00:29:29,548 --> 00:29:31,698
Whatever our man is up to
will happen on Easter eve.

348
00:29:31,550 --> 00:29:35,702
That's only about a week away.
Maybe this is almost over.

349
00:29:35,554 --> 00:29:39,706
Or maybe in our perp's mind
that's when it really begins.

350
00:29:39,558 --> 00:29:41,708
No, last night.

351
00:29:41,560 --> 00:29:45,712
I had just taken a blood sample
when she ran off.

352
00:29:47,566 --> 00:29:51,718
How could her
paperwork disappear?

353
00:29:52,571 --> 00:29:56,723
I just need her name.
Allright, thanks.

354
00:30:40,619 --> 00:30:44,771
[Rustling]

355
00:30:46,625 --> 00:30:50,777
[Cody]
Mim!

356
00:30:51,630 --> 00:30:55,782
[Screaming]
Mim!

357
00:30:55,634 --> 00:30:59,786
[ Hissing, Squealing ]

358
00:30:59,638 --> 00:31:03,790
Mim!

359
00:31:04,643 --> 00:31:08,795
Mim!

360
00:31:15,654 --> 00:31:19,806
[Stops]

361
00:31:24,663 --> 00:31:28,815
[Cody]
Mim!

362
00:31:32,671 --> 00:31:35,822
Cody.

363
00:31:35,674 --> 00:31:35,674
Cody.

364
00:31:35,674 --> 00:31:37,824
It's okay.
It's okay.

365
00:31:37,676 --> 00:31:41,828
- Bad dream.
- Yeah, me too.

366
00:31:42,681 --> 00:31:44,831
Me too.

367
00:31:44,683 --> 00:31:46,833
You try to go
to sleep, okay?

368
00:31:46,685 --> 00:31:50,837
Okay?

369
00:31:51,690 --> 00:31:55,842
Buenas noches, mi angelito.

370
00:32:18,717 --> 00:32:22,869
I think I'll take Cody shopping
today. It's so beautiful outside.

371
00:32:22,721 --> 00:32:26,873
Okay. I'll just
finish this and go home.

372
00:32:27,726 --> 00:32:30,877
Maria, are you
missing your rosary?

373
00:32:30,729 --> 00:32:32,879
No. Why?

374
00:32:32,731 --> 00:32:35,882
Because I found it
under Cody's pillow last night.

375
00:32:35,734 --> 00:32:38,885
Oh, she asked me for it.

376
00:32:38,737 --> 00:32:41,888
It makes her feel better.

377
00:32:41,740 --> 00:32:45,892
-I have an extra one if you want it.
-No, thank you.

378
00:32:46,745 --> 00:32:49,896
I'll bring it for you
just in case.

379
00:32:49,748 --> 00:32:53,900
Cody, you ready to go
shopping with your Mim?

380
00:32:59,758 --> 00:33:02,909
What?

381
00:33:02,761 --> 00:33:06,913
- Is that Maria's church?
- Yes. Can we go?

382
00:33:06,765 --> 00:33:10,917
Okay, let's go.

383
00:33:24,783 --> 00:33:28,935
I'm going to say a little prayer,
like Maria does, okay?

384
00:34:03,822 --> 00:34:06,973
Cody?

385
00:34:06,825 --> 00:34:10,977
[ Candles Rattling ]

386
00:34:24,843 --> 00:34:28,995
[Rattling Stops]

387
00:34:57,876 --> 00:35:02,028
She's sad, Mim. So sad.

388
00:35:02,881 --> 00:35:07,033
She's crying for us.

389
00:35:06,885 --> 00:35:11,037
It's okay.
It's okay.

390
00:35:25,904 --> 00:35:30,056
- Nice limo you got there.
- You won the lottery?

391
00:35:30,909 --> 00:35:33,059
- Miss O'Connor?
- Yes.

392
00:35:32,911 --> 00:35:37,063
Honey.

393
00:35:38,917 --> 00:35:41,067
Hello, Mags.

394
00:35:40,919 --> 00:35:45,071
Hi, Cody. Do you have a kiss
