397
00:35:55,934 --> 00:35:59,085
We just got back
from Barbados last week.

398
00:35:58,937 --> 00:36:02,088
Part honeymoon,
part healing process for Jenna.

399
00:36:01,940 --> 00:36:04,090
And no more bad habits--

400
00:36:03,942 --> 00:36:07,093
- except for spending Eric's money.
- Mm-hmm.

401
00:36:06,945 --> 00:36:09,095
He saved my life.

402
00:36:08,947 --> 00:36:13,099
- Are you a doctor?
- He's Eric Stark, Maggie.

403
00:36:13,952 --> 00:36:17,103
The New Dawn,
the foundation, the seminars.

404
00:36:16,955 --> 00:36:21,107
Did you meet Jenna through
your work, Mr. Stark?

405
00:36:20,959 --> 00:36:24,110
Eric, please. Yeah, we met
at one of my outreach centers.

406
00:36:23,962 --> 00:36:26,112
- When was it, only last month?
- [Jenna Giggling]

407
00:36:25,964 --> 00:36:29,115
- Isn't that amazing?
- Crazy.

408
00:36:28,967 --> 00:36:32,118
So this is all happening
very quickly.

409
00:36:31,970 --> 00:36:34,120
Oh, yeah.
Idon't waste time anymore.

410
00:36:33,972 --> 00:36:36,122
I wasted half my life on drugs.
That was enough.

411
00:36:35,974 --> 00:36:40,126
No more.
No more presents.

412
00:36:39,978 --> 00:36:42,128
Um.

413
00:36:41,980 --> 00:36:45,131
There's still something
wrong with her, isn't there?

414
00:36:44,983 --> 00:36:49,135
-I was hoped she would outgrow this.
-She's fine.

415
00:36:48,987 --> 00:36:53,139
Just a little different.
And she certainly isn't deaf.

416
00:36:53,992 --> 00:36:58,144
You know, I'm a little bit
in a state of shock here.

417
00:36:57,996 --> 00:37:00,146
You must know, Eric,
that I haven't seen my sister...

418
00:36:59,998 --> 00:37:03,149
since the first week
Cody was born.

419
00:37:03,001 --> 00:37:06,152
Well, I'm here now,
and I'm healthy.

420
00:37:06,004 --> 00:37:09,155
And everything's going to be fine,
isn't it, sweetie?

421
00:37:09,007 --> 00:37:10,156
We'll get you well.

422
00:37:10,008 --> 00:37:13,159
- Do you have a kiss for Mommy, hmm?
- No.

423
00:37:13,011 --> 00:37:17,163
She has to get used to you.
That will take time.

424
00:37:19,017 --> 00:37:21,167
Mm-hmm.

425
00:37:21,019 --> 00:37:23,169
Like round-the-clock time, huh?

426
00:37:23,021 --> 00:37:26,172
- Cody?
- Well, that's why we're here.

427
00:37:26,024 --> 00:37:28,174
You're gonna come live
with Eric and me, Cody.

428
00:37:28,026 --> 00:37:32,178
- We're gonna take you home.
- Darling?

429
00:37:32,030 --> 00:37:35,181
Why don't you have Dahnia
come up from the limo?

430
00:37:35,033 --> 00:37:39,185
- Maybe Cody would like to meet her.
- We have a wonderful nanny.

431
00:37:39,037 --> 00:37:42,188
Cody, go in my room
and watch cartoons, okay, sweetie?

432
00:37:42,040 --> 00:37:46,192
- [Dialing Phone]
- Hi. Could you send Dahnia up now?

433
00:37:48,046 --> 00:37:51,197
Jenna, I don't think
you understand.

434
00:37:51,049 --> 00:37:55,201
- Cody's very special.
- You just said she was fine.

435
00:37:55,053 --> 00:37:58,204
Yes, but she probably
has a form of autism.

436
00:37:58,056 --> 00:38:01,207
-I want the right people to see her.
-She's with the right people.

437
00:38:01,059 --> 00:38:05,211
It's taken a lot of work
to bring her to this point.

438
00:38:05,063 --> 00:38:07,213
A change could
undo everything.

439
00:38:07,065 --> 00:38:11,217
Mags, Eric and I talked about this.
She's my daughter.

440
00:38:12,070 --> 00:38:16,222
And it's sort of like--

441
00:38:16,074 --> 00:38:18,224
It's not really up to you.

442
00:38:18,076 --> 00:38:22,228
Who do you think raised her when you
left her like a piece of luggage?

443
00:38:22,080 --> 00:38:25,231
Who paid for her doctors
and her schools and her test?

444
00:38:25,083 --> 00:38:27,233
That gives me some say
what happens to her.

445
00:38:27,085 --> 00:38:28,234
Of course it does, Maggie.

446
00:38:28,086 --> 00:38:32,238
We're grateful that you took care
of Cody when Jenna wasn't able to,

447
00:38:33,091 --> 00:38:35,241
but now she is.

448
00:38:35,093 --> 00:38:36,242
And I have the money to give her...

449
00:38:36,094 --> 00:38:39,245
the kind of special care
and schooling she needs.

450
00:38:39,097 --> 00:38:43,249
Now that you're here,
I want you both to be in her life.

451
00:38:43,101 --> 00:38:47,253
She's made so much progress,
but what she needs right now...

452
00:38:47,105 --> 00:38:48,254
are rules and stability
and familiar faces.

453
00:38:48,106 --> 00:38:51,257
