00:40:59,237 --> 00:41:01,387
Six years old.

485
00:41:01,239 --> 00:41:03,389
- It's her niece actually.
- Can I take a look at that?

486
00:41:03,241 --> 00:41:05,391
Yeah.

487
00:41:05,243 --> 00:41:09,395
Anyway, the kid's not really
missing. It's a custody dispute.

488
00:41:09,247 --> 00:41:11,397
We should probably
give it to Social Services.

489
00:41:11,249 --> 00:41:14,400
Eric Stark is involved in this?
Have you talked to this guy?

490
00:41:14,252 --> 00:41:16,402
- No.
- I tried. His number is unlisted...

491
00:41:16,254 --> 00:41:18,404
and the foundation
just gave me the runaround.

492
00:41:18,256 --> 00:41:20,406
- Want me to find a number on him?
- Yeah, thanks.

493
00:41:20,258 --> 00:41:23,409
I'd like to talk to Miss O'Connor
for a few minutes.

494
00:41:23,261 --> 00:41:27,413
Please, come this way.

495
00:41:29,267 --> 00:41:31,417
I'll be honest with you,
Miss O'Connor,

496
00:41:31,269 --> 00:41:34,420
Stark's organization has been
under investigation before.

497
00:41:34,272 --> 00:41:37,423
For what?

498
00:41:37,275 --> 00:41:40,426
Harboring runaways.

499
00:41:40,278 --> 00:41:42,428
There were allegations
of tax fraud...

500
00:41:42,280 --> 00:41:44,430
and money laundering,
but nothing that would stick.

501
00:41:44,282 --> 00:41:48,434
Please, sit down.

502
00:41:48,286 --> 00:41:51,437
See, Stark is well
protected politically...

503
00:41:51,289 --> 00:41:54,440
and he keeps a pack of high-priced
lawyers in attack mode year round.

504
00:41:54,292 --> 00:41:56,442
Are you saying
you're scared of him?

505
00:41:56,294 --> 00:41:58,444
All I'm saying
is that he'll bury you...

506
00:41:58,296 --> 00:42:01,447
if you come
after him without grounds.

507
00:42:01,299 --> 00:42:04,450
Are those
the serial murders?

508
00:42:04,302 --> 00:42:07,453
I'm advising a task force here
that's handling that investigation.

509
00:42:07,305 --> 00:42:09,455
But you don't think this
has anything to do with--

510
00:42:09,307 --> 00:42:11,457
No, but I do think...

511
00:42:11,309 --> 00:42:15,461
that what my charmless colleague
told you before is probably true.

512
00:42:15,313 --> 00:42:16,462
Right now the best thing
for you to do...

513
00:42:16,314 --> 00:42:20,466
is try to establish
some form of legal custody.

514
00:42:20,318 --> 00:42:24,470
- You need a lawyer, not a cop.
- So that's it? ''Get a lawyer''?

515
00:42:24,322 --> 00:42:26,472
That's all the help
you have to offer me?

516
00:42:26,324 --> 00:42:28,474
No, you have my word.
I will follow up on Stark.

517
00:42:28,326 --> 00:42:31,477
It'll be my pleasure.
I think his whole outfit stinks.

518
00:42:31,329 --> 00:42:34,480
But I want you to promise me
if you reach him first--

519
00:42:34,332 --> 00:42:36,482
I would just feel better
if you give me a call...

520
00:42:36,334 --> 00:42:38,484
before you even talk to this guy.

521
00:42:38,336 --> 00:42:42,488
That will be my first priority,
Agent, making you feel better.

522
00:42:43,341 --> 00:42:46,492
Miss O'Connor.
Miss O'Connor.

523
00:42:46,344 --> 00:42:50,496
The only thing I can get on Stark
is the number for his lawyer.

524
00:42:50,348 --> 00:42:52,498
- [Door Shuts]
- No, thanks.

525
00:42:52,350 --> 00:42:54,500
I want to follow up
on this one.

526
00:42:54,352 --> 00:42:58,504
- [ Chuckling ] Yeah, right.
- What's that supposed to mean?

527
00:42:58,356 --> 00:42:59,505
Come on. The one lead
you're gonna follow up on...

528
00:42:59,357 --> 00:43:02,508
is attached to a piece of tail
like that?

529
00:43:02,360 --> 00:43:06,512
No wonder this priest
thing didn't work out.

530
00:43:06,364 --> 00:43:10,516
This may be
the best lead we've got.

531
00:43:11,369 --> 00:43:15,521
Take a look, Frank.
December 16, 1993.

532
00:43:17,375 --> 00:43:21,527
The same birthday
as every kid on that board.

533
00:43:58,416 --> 00:44:01,567
May I help you?

534
00:44:01,419 --> 00:44:03,569
I really don't know much
about your program and--

535
00:44:03,421 --> 00:44:04,570
Would you like a tour?

536
00:44:04,422 --> 00:44:08,574
Our main focus has been our national
youth crusade, but our programs...

537
00:44:08,426 --> 00:44:12,578
for adults have been gaining more
and more popularity.

538
00:44:12,430 --> 00:44:16,582
Our self-realization seminars
only require a $400 donation.

539
00:44:16,434 --> 00:44:20,586
What I'm really interested in
is speaking with Eric Stark.

540
00:44:20,438 --> 00:44:23,589
His schedule doesn't allow
for personal interviews,

541
00:44:23,441 --> 00:44:25,591
but I'll take you
to our computer lounge...

542
00:44:25,443 --> 00:44:27,593
and you can e-mail him directly.

543
00:44:27,445 --> 00:44:31,597
Before I found New Dawn, I didn't
have any respect for myself.

544
00:44:31,449 --> 00:44:33,599
I didn't think
I mattered to anybody.

545
00:44:33,451 --> 00:44:36,602
And Eric helped me learn
to will what I do...

546
00:44:36,454 --> 00:44:38,604
and to stop letting
others judge me.

547
00:44:38,456 --> 00:44:42,608
[ Man ]
Eric helps you tap into this power.

548
00:44:42,460 --> 00:44:46,612
I mean, he changed
my whole life.

549
00:44:59,477 --> 00:45:03,629
[ThunderRumbling]

550
00:45:27,505 --> 00:45:29,655
[Answering Machine Beeps]

551
00:45:29,507 --> 00:45:33,659
Maggie, this is Cheri Post. I got
your number from the hospital.

552
00:45:33,511 --> 00:45:35,661
I know where the kid is.

553
00:45:35,513 --> 00:45:38,664
Meet me at the diner
at Stanton and Essex at midnight.

554
00:45:38,516 --> 00:45:42,668
Do me a favor.
Bring some cash, okay?

555
00:45:47,525 --> 00:45:51,677
This is all you brought?
I can't get out of the city on this.

556
00:45:51,529 --> 00:45:53,679
Cheri, where is she?

557
00:45:56,534 --> 00:45:59,685
Literally?
Of course not.

558
00:45:59,537 --> 00:46:03,689
Well, Eric does-- and so do
the sick fucks that are in with him.

559
00:46:03,541 --> 00:46:06,692
So would you if you'd
seen what I've seen.

560
00:46:06,544 --> 00:46:10,696
- Like what?
- Eric's got this religion,

561
00:46:11,549 --> 00:46:14,700
only it's more like
the opposite of religion.

562
00:46:14,552 --> 00:46:17,703
I thought it was all bullshit
at first, but I've seen it work.

563
00:46:17,555 --> 00:46:19,705
They can predict
the future,

564
00:46:19,557 --> 00:46:23,709
even make things happen
to people, bad things.

565
00:46:24,562 --> 00:46:26,712
What does this
have to do with Cody?

566
00:46:26,564 --> 00:46:30,716
About a year ago, they all started
acting a lot weirder than usual.

567
00:46:31,569 --> 00:46:34,720
They started hunting down kids--

568
00:46:34,572 --> 00:46:38,724
six-year-old kids, boys, girls.

569
00:46:39,577 --> 00:46:41,727
But they all had to be born
on this certain date.

570
00:46:41,579 --> 00:46:45,731
They'd take each kid
and put them through this test,

571
00:46:46,584 --> 00:46:50,736
and if they failed,
they'd kill them.

572
00:46:51,589 --> 00:46:55,741
''The slaughter of the innocents,''
they called it.

573
00:46:55,593 --> 00:46:58,744
Only Cody isn't like
the other ones.

574
00:46:58,596 --> 00:47:01,747
She's the one they've
been looking for all along.

575
00:47:01,599 --> 00:47:05,751
So instead of killing her,
Eric's gonna try to change her--

576
00:47:06,604 --> 00:47:08,754
to make her just like him.

577
00:47:08,606 --> 00:47:11,757
See? So he can use her power.

578
00:47:11,609 --> 00:47:14,760
She's just a little girl.

579
00:47:14,612 --> 00:47:16,762
She's more than that,
at least she's gonna be.

580
00:47:16,614 --> 00:47:19,765
Gonna be what?

581
00:47:19,617 --> 00:47:22,768
I don't know.
A saint, a prophet.

582
00:47:22,620 --> 00:47:26,772
She's gonna lead people to God,
Maggie-- a lot of people--

583
00:47:27,625 --> 00:47:31,777
only Eric
won't let that happen.

584
00:47:31,629 --> 00:47:34,780
If he can't turn her,
he'll kill her.

585
00:47:34,632 --> 00:47:38,784
- Cheri, where is she?
- [ThunderRumbling]

586
00:47:46,644 --> 00:47:48,794
Do you promise
to get her out of there?

587
00:47:48,646 --> 00:47:52,798
- Yes.
- You're gonna need this.

588
00:47:52,650 --> 00:47:56,802
[Thunderclap]

589
00:48:33,691 --> 00:48:37,843
[Man Laughs]

590
00:48:42,700 --> 00:48:46,852
Hello. Hello?

591
00:48:58,716 --> 00:49:02,868
[ Screaming ]

592
00:49:05,723 --> 00:49:09,875
[ Shrieks ]

593
00:50:04,782 --> 00:50:08,934
Cheri.

594
00:50:11,789 --> 00:50:15,941
[ Screaming ]

595
00:50:25,803 --> 00:50:28,954
Come in. Crazy people
like an audience.

596
00:50:28,806 --> 00:50:30,956
Is that a self-diagnosis?

597
00:50:30,808 --> 00:50:33,959
No, just
a popular theory.

598
00:50:33,811 --> 00:50:37,963
I had a half a dozen transit
cops here this morning.

599
00:50:37,815 --> 00:50:41,967
They think the concussion makes me
a less-than-credible witness.

600
00:50:42,820 --> 00:50:46,972
They're having a hard time believing
you because they didn't find a body.

601
00:50:48,826 --> 00:50:50,976
- You lied to me.
- Excuse me?

602
00:50:50,828 --> 00:50:53,979
You think what's happened to Cody
is connected with the murders.

603
00:50:53,831 --> 00:50:55,981
How many children are dead?

604
00:50:55,833 --> 00:50:58,984
Five, that we know of.

605
00:50:58,836 --> 00:51:02,988
''Slaughter of the innocents.''
Does that ring a bell?

606
00:51:02,840 --> 00:51:04,990
- Where did you hear that?
- From the girl they killed.

607
00:51:04,842 --> 00:51:08,994
- What did she mean?
- Well, it's from the Bible.

608
00:51:09,847 --> 00:51:12,998
When the three wise men
told King Herod...

609
00:51:12,850 --> 00:51:15,000
that the star over Bethlehem...

610
00:51:14,852 --> 00:51:18,003
was the sign that
the Son of God had been born,

611
00:51:17,855 --> 00:51:20,005
Herod sent his soldiers
to kill all of the children...

612
00:51:19,857 --> 00:51:21,006
that were born on that date.

613
00:51:20,858 --> 00:51:23,008
But then an angel appeared
before Mary and Joseph...

614
00:51:22,860 --> 00:51:25,010
and warned them to escape.

615
00:51:24,862 --> 00:51:28,013
And what date
are our innocents born on?

616
00:51:27,865 --> 00:51:30,015
- December 16, '93.
- You son of a bitch.

617
00:51:29,867 --> 00:51:32,017
- It's different with Cody.
- You should have told me!

618
00:51:31,869 --> 00:51:34,019
It's different with Cody.
We know who took her.

619
00:51:33,871 --> 00:51:36,021
And you haven't done
anything about it.

620
00:51:35,873 --> 00:51:38,023
Have you even found where
he's keeping her?

621
00:51:37,875 --> 00:51:40,025
Maggie, his organization owns...

622
00:51:39,877 --> 00:51:42,027
dozens of different properties
all around the country.

623
00:51:41,879 --> 00:51:45,030
He lives like a textbook paranoid.
He keeps moving all the time.

624
00:51:44,882 --> 00:51:46,031
You could put out a warrant.

625
00:51:45,883 --> 00:51:48,033
Come on, Maggie.
You don't think I want this guy?

626
00:51:47,885 --> 00:51:51,036
I do. But if I make a move without
grounds, it'll blow the whole case.

627
00:51:50,888 --> 00:51:54,039
And there won't be
a second chance here--

628
00:51:53,891 --> 00:51:58,043
not for you,
not for Cody.

629
00:52:00,898 --> 00:52:02,047
That's a composite
that we got of the killer...

630
00:52:01,899 --> 00:52:05,050
from two very strong eyewitnesses.

631
00:52:04,902 --> 00:52:08,053
- Do you recognize him?
- No.

632
00:52:07,905 --> 00:52:12,057
- But Eric could still be involved.
- Yeah, it's possible.

633
00:52:11,909 --> 00:52:15,060
How many children have been killed
since Cody disappeared?

634
00:52:14,912 --> 00:52:17,062
None.

635
00:52:16,914 --> 00:52:20,065
I'm going to help you,
Maggie.

636
00:52:19,917 --> 00:52:22,067
I'm gonna make a request to have
an officer outside the door...

637
00:52:21,919 --> 00:52:25,070
- for the next couple of days, okay?
- Okay.

638
00:52:24,922 --> 00:52:29,074
There is one other thing.

639
00:52:28,926 --> 00:52:32,077
The hospital said
that they found this on you.

640
00:52:31,929 --> 00:52:36,081
Those kids tried to kill me
last night. I wish I had used it.

641
00:52:41,939 --> 00:52:46,091
Well, you didn't
get that from me.

642
00:53:34,992 --> 00:53:39,144
Lord, I could use
a little help here.

643
00:53:40,998 --> 00:53:43,148
[Rustling]

644
00:53:43,000 --> 00:53:45,150
Oh, sorry.
You all alone in here?

645
00:53:45,002 --> 00:53:48,153
- Yeah.
- Look, if I'm disturbing you--

646
00:53:48,005 --> 00:53:52,157
No, that's okay.
I'm done for tonight.

647
00:53:56,013 --> 00:54:00,165
Oh, man.

648
00:54:00,017 --> 00:54:02,167
- I don't know how you do this.
- What?

649
00:54:02,019 --> 00:54:06,171
This kind of work.
Day after day.

650
00:54:07,024 --> 00:54:09,174
It's gotta wear down
a man's spirit.

651
00:54:09,026 --> 00:54:13,178
The worst thing is knowing
that he's still out there.

652
00:54:13,030 --> 00:54:17,182
And we're running out of time.

653
00:54:17,034 --> 00:54:19,184
You'll catch him.

654
00:54:19,036 --> 00:54:23,188
- I got a good feeling about this.
- You do, huh?

655
00:54:25,042 --> 00:54:29,194
You're wrong
about one thing though.

656
00:54:31,048 --> 00:54:33,198
What's that?

657
00:54:33,050 --> 00:54:36,201
You're not working
alone tonight.

658
00:54:36,053 --> 00:54:40,205
A good man is never
alone in this world.

659
00:55:11,088 --> 00:55:15,240
I'm sorry.
Can't you tell me who she is?

660
00:55:35,112 --> 00:55:39,264
[ Chattering, Indistinct ]

661
00:55:55,132 --> 00:55:59,284
Hey, how about
watching my car?

662
00:56:31,168 --> 00:56:35,320
[Whispering, Indistinct]

663
00:56:39,176 --> 00:56:43,328
[ Shrieking ]

664
00:56:47,184 --> 00:56:50,335
- [ Squawking ]
- [ Chittering ]

665
00:56:50,187 --> 00:56:54,339
[Clanking]

666
00:57:11,208 --> 00:57:15,360
Hello?

667
00:57:15,212 --> 00:57:18,363
Jenna, it's Maggie.

668
00:57:18,215 --> 00:57:20,365
[Footsteps]

669
00:57:20,217 --> 00:57:23,368
Maggie, if Eric
finds you here--

670
00:57:23,220 --> 00:57:25,370
Do you have any idea
who this man is?

671
00:57:25,222 --> 00:57:29,374
- Maggie, I'm begging you.
- Cody. Cody.

672
00:57:29,226 --> 00:57:33,378
Cody, hi.
Hi!

673
00:57:34,231 --> 00:57:38,383
- Cody miss Mim.
- I missed you. Are you all right?

674
00:57:39,236 --> 00:57:43,388
Cody go
to dentist tomorrow.

675
00:57:43,240 --> 00:57:45,390
Tell 'em don't make
Cody go to dentist.

676
00:57:45,242 --> 00:57:48,393
No. How would you like
to get up right now and leave?

677
00:57:48,245 --> 00:57:52,397
- What do you think you're doing?
- I'm taking Cody.

678
00:57:52,249 --> 00:57:56,401
- And I want you to come with us.
- No. No, Maggie.

679
00:57:56,253 --> 00:57:58,403
No. Maggie, I've watched him
with her. He's very gentle.

680
00:57:58,255 --> 00:57:59,404
Maggie.

681
00:57:59,256 --> 00:58:03,408
What a surprise.
You should've called.

682
00:58:03,260 --> 00:58:06,411
Unfortunately, it's almost time
for Cody's nap.

683
00:58:06,263 --> 00:58:09,414
Come here, Cody.

684
00:58:09,266 --> 00:58:11,416
Sit down, Maggie.

685
00:58:11,268 --> 00:58:13,418
It's allright, Jenna.
It's okay.

686
00:58:13,270 --> 00:58:14,419
Actually, uh,

687
00:58:14,271 --> 00:58:18,423
- I'm a little tired myself.
- [Eric]No! Stay.

688
00:58:19,276 --> 00:58:23,428
We'll have drinks.
Stuart!

689
00:58:23,280 --> 00:58:26,431
Stuart!

690
00:58:26,283 --> 00:58:30,435
I think Maggie'd
like a drink.

691
00:58:30,287 --> 00:58:34,439
Oh--
Unless you have to run.

692
00:58:36,293 --> 00:58:39,444
No. I'll stay.

693
00:58:39,296 --> 00:58:43,448
I don't care
for a drink.

694
00:58:43,300 --> 00:58:46,451
I've been trying to reach you
for the last couple of days,

695
00:58:46,303 --> 00:58:48,453
and I really don't
understand why--

696
00:58:48,305 --> 00:58:50,455
There are certain forces
in this country, Maggie,

697
00:58:50,307 --> 00:58:54,459
that don't want me empowering
the younger generation.

698
00:58:54,311 --> 00:58:58,463
I have to protect my privacy
and my family any way I can.

699
00:59:01,318 --> 00:59:04,469
Well, the reason
I dropped by is, um,

700
00:59:04,321 --> 00:59:06,471
they're having an Easter egg
hunt at Cody's old school.

701
00:59:06,323 --> 00:59:09,474
And I thought it would
be really fun if we went.

702
00:59:09,326 --> 00:59:11,476
- Why don't you run get your coat?
- Actually, Maggie,

703
00:59:11,328 --> 00:59:14,479
things have changed
since last time we spoke.

704
00:59:14,331 --> 00:59:18,483
Originally, we'd hoped some kind
of visitation might be worked out,

705
00:59:18,335 --> 00:59:20,485
but your attitude
has made that impossible.

706
00:59:20,337 --> 00:59:24,489
[ Sighs ]
I knew you wouldn't give her up...

707
00:59:25,342 --> 00:59:28,493
without getting
something in return.

708
00:59:28,345 --> 00:59:32,497
- You have nothing I want.
- How about my silence?

709
00:59:33,350 --> 00:59:36,501
- Go on.
- I'm no fool, Eric.

710
00:59:36,353 --> 00:59:39,504
I didn't imagine what
happened to Cheri.

711
00:59:39,356 --> 00:59:43,508
- I know she's dead.
- No one's saying you're a fool.

712
00:59:43,360 --> 00:59:46,511
It's just obvious you're not well.
[ Chuckles ]

713
00:59:46,363 --> 00:59:50,515
So, I'm scared.
You've accomplished that.

714
00:59:51,368 --> 00:59:55,520
But I'm not likely to make a deal
and break it the way she did, am I?

715
00:59:55,372 --> 00:59:59,524
You let me take Cody and Jenna
and leave right now,

716
00:59:59,376 --> 01:00:02,527
and that's it--
it's over.

717
01:00:02,379 --> 01:00:04,529
You can go on with your
mission or your religion...

718
01:00:04,381 --> 01:00:07,532
or whatever it is, and you'll
never hear from us again.

719
01:00:07,384 --> 01:00:11,536
Maggie, I'm not leaving.
There's nothing bad going on here.

720
01:00:11,388 --> 01:00:13,538
We are taking
very good care of Cody.

721
01:00:13,390 --> 01:00:14,539
Eric gives her
everything she needs.

722
01:00:14,391 --> 01:00:17,542
- He married you to get to her.
- You are jealous.

723
01:00:17,394 --> 01:00:21,546
You are jealous because I finally
have a family and you don't!

724
01:00:21,398 --> 01:00:25,550
Maggie, this is exactly why
I didn't want you here.

725
01:00:25,402 --> 01:00:29,554
Dahnia,
take Cody upstairs!

726
01:00:35,412 --> 01:00:38,563
I've never fired
a gun before,

727
01:00:38,415 --> 01:00:42,567
but I'll bet
at this range I'm dead on.

728
01:00:44,421 --> 01:00:48,573
Don't!

729
01:00:51,428 --> 01:00:53,578
Are you really gonna
shoot me, Maggie?

730
01:00:53,430 --> 01:00:57,582
[ Chuckles ]
Right here, in front of Cody?

731
01:00:59,436 --> 01:01:03,588
Close your eyes, sweetheart.

732
01:01:04,441 --> 01:01:08,593
Go ahead
and fire, Maggie.

733
01:01:09,446 --> 01:01:13,598
[ Whispering ]
Feel that hate.

734
01:01:13,450 --> 01:01:17,602
Feel it?
Feels good, doesn 't it?

735
01:01:18,455 --> 01:01:21,606
Something that feels
that good...

736
01:01:21,458 --> 01:01:24,609
can't be wrong.

737
01:01:24,461 --> 01:01:27,612
[ Hammer Clicking ]

738
01:01:27,464 --> 01:01:29,614
[ Panicked Breathing ]
Oh, my God.

739
01:01:29,466 --> 01:01:32,617
Oh--

740
01:01:32,469 --> 01:01:36,621
Thou... shalt...
not... kill.

741
01:01:39,476 --> 01:01:43,628
- Especially without bullets.
- [Bullets Clattering]

742
01:01:44,481 --> 01:01:46,631
I know. You're confused,
aren't you?

743
01:01:46,483 --> 01:01:50,635
- [ Whimpers ]
- Concussions are tricky, huh?

744
01:01:51,488 --> 01:01:55,640
They can mess
with your perceptions.

745
01:01:55,492 --> 01:01:59,644
Police start saying
you're seeing things.

746
01:01:59,496 --> 01:02:03,648
Maybe you are.

747
01:02:03,500 --> 01:02:04,649
- Oh.
- Here.

748
01:02:04,501 --> 01:02:06,651
- Oh.
- Here.

749
01:02:06,503 --> 01:02:08,653
I wouldn't want
you to hurt yourself.

750
01:02:08,505 --> 01:02:11,656
You know what?

751
01:02:11,508 --> 01:02:14,659
On second thought,

752
01:02:14,511 --> 01:02:17,662
I think I will take
your silence after all.

753
01:02:17,514 --> 01:02:20,665
[ Muffled Cries ]

754
01:02:20,517 --> 01:02:24,669
Mim!

755
01:02:24,521 --> 01:02:28,673
Mim!

756
01:03:00,557 --> 01:03:04,709
-[ Gasps ]
-[ Horns Blaring, Tires Screeching ]

757
01:03:11,568 --> 01:03:15,720
- [ Tires Screeching ]
- [ Pedal Thumping ]

758
01:03:27,584 --> 01:03:30,735
[ Hissing ]

759
01:03:30,587 --> 01:03:34,739
[Metal Groaning, Breaking]

760
01:03:38,595 --> 01:03:42,747
[Metal Creaking]

761
01:03:42,599 --> 01:03:46,751
[Gasping]

762
01:03:47,604 --> 01:03:51,756
- [ Horns Honking ]
- [ Onlookers Clamoring ]

763
01:03:54,611 --> 01:03:58,763
You've got to get out.
Take my hand.

764
01:04:01,618 --> 01:04:05,770
[ Metal Scraping ]

765
01:04:15,632 --> 01:04:19,784
[Metal Groaning]

766
01:04:35,652 --> 01:04:37,802
[Sirens Wailing]

767
01:04:37,654 --> 01:04:41,806
[People Chattering]

768
01:04:42,659 --> 01:04:46,811
[ Ringing ]

769
01:04:46,663 --> 01:04:48,813
- Agent Travis.
- It's Maggie.

770
01:04:48,665 --> 01:04:51,816
What the hell happened to you?
We thought you were dead.

771
01:04:51,668 --> 01:04:54,819
We've got witnesses that saw
your car go into the river.

772
01:04:54,671 --> 01:04:57,822
-Someone helped me. No one saw that?
-I guess not.

773
01:04:57,674 --> 01:04:59,824
And lucky for you.
If the cops found you at the scene,

774
01:04:59,676 --> 01:05:01,826
you'd be in a cell right now.

775
01:05:01,678 --> 01:05:02,827
There'd be a warrant
out for hit-and-run...

776
01:05:02,679 --> 01:05:05,830
- if they knew you were alive.
- It was Stark and his people.

777
01:05:05,682 --> 01:05:08,833
- I went there to get Cody.
- You what?

778
01:05:08,685 --> 01:05:10,835
- How did you manage--
- They drugged me.

779
01:05:10,687 --> 01:05:14,839
I don't know how, but I woke up
right before the crash.

780
01:05:15,692 --> 01:05:18,843
You do believe me,
don't you?

781
01:05:18,695 --> 01:05:21,846
Maggie, I want you
to turn yourself in to me.

782
01:05:21,698 --> 01:05:24,849
At least you'll be safe until
we can build a case against Stark.

783
01:05:24,701 --> 01:05:28,853
You gotta trust me right now.
Trust me.

784
01:05:28,705 --> 01:05:31,856
- You want me to be safe?
- Yes, I do.

785
01:05:31,708 --> 01:05:33,858
Then don't tell
anybody I'm alive.

786
01:05:33,710 --> 01:05:37,862
- Maggie, don't-don't--
- [ Dial Tone ]

787
01:05:50,727 --> 01:05:52,877
Cody?

788
01:05:52,729 --> 01:05:56,881
Come on.

789
01:06:00,737 --> 01:06:04,889
You're not like
ordinary children, Cody.

790
01:06:04,741 --> 01:06:06,891
Do you know that?

791
01:06:06,743 --> 01:06:10,895
On the night
you were born...

792
01:06:10,747 --> 01:06:13,898
a star appeared
in the sky...

793
01:06:13,750 --> 01:06:16,901
pointed right
down at you.

794
01:06:16,753 --> 01:06:20,905
A star that hadn't
been seen in 2,000 years.

795
01:06:20,757 --> 01:06:23,908
Like baby Jesus?

796
01:06:23,760 --> 01:06:27,912
You're such a smart girl.

797
01:06:27,764 --> 01:06:31,916
- Do you love God, Cody?
- Yes.

798
01:06:31,768 --> 01:06:34,919
Well, maybe that's just 'cause
you think you're supposed to.

799
01:06:34,771 --> 01:06:38,923
I'm gonna teach you
something tonight.

800
01:06:42,779 --> 01:06:46,931
Something I think
you're smart enough to understand.

801
01:06:48,785 --> 01:06:52,937
[Muttering]
No. no. No, no. Shoo. Uh-uh. Sh--

802
01:06:52,789 --> 01:06:56,941
- Look at this man.
- [Muttering Continues]

803
01:06:58,795 --> 01:07:02,947
- He should be in an institution.
- No, no. No, no.

804
01:07:02,799 --> 01:07:05,950
Shoo.
Uh-uh. Go away!

805
01:07:05,802 --> 01:07:09,954
But God abandoned him,
didn't He?

806
01:07:11,808 --> 01:07:15,960
Left him here to suffer.

807
01:07:16,813 --> 01:07:20,965
- Death... would be a kinder fate.
- Shoo-shoo!

808
01:07:21,818 --> 01:07:25,970
- Even a cruel death.
- [ Muttering ]

809
01:07:25,822 --> 01:07:29,974
Through the power
of the one I serve,

810
01:07:29,826 --> 01:07:33,978
I can give him the strength
to end his pain.

811
01:07:56,853 --> 01:08:01,005
[ Speaking Foreign Language ]

812
01:08:08,865 --> 01:08:13,017
- [Continues]
- [Stick Scraping]

813
01:08:14,871 --> 01:08:19,023
[ Continuing ]

814
01:08:50,907 --> 01:08:55,059
Watch.

815
01:08:55,912 --> 01:08:59,063
If God loves his children so much,
maybe he'll stop this.

816
01:08:58,915 --> 01:09:03,067
Redeem him...
somehow.

817
01:09:03,920 --> 01:09:06,070
Or maybe...

818
01:09:05,922 --> 01:09:05,922
Or maybe...

819
01:09:05,922 --> 01:09:09,073
the release
I've offered him...

820
01:09:08,925 --> 01:09:13,077
is his only
true salvation.

821
01:09:25,942 --> 01:09:30,094
Eric!

822
01:09:51,968 --> 01:09:56,120
[ Whispering ]
He has forgotten you.

823
01:10:02,979 --> 01:10:07,131
Th--
Thank you.

824
01:10:06,983 --> 01:10:11,135
[ Chuckles ]

825
01:10:25,001 --> 01:10:29,153
She will be ours.

826
01:10:49,025 --> 01:10:51,175
Dear God,

827
01:10:51,027 --> 01:10:55,179
if You really are there,
please help me.

828
01:10:56,032 --> 01:11:00,184
Please
help me and Cody.

829
01:11:07,043 --> 01:11:11,195
I know what's
happening to you.

830
01:11:11,047 --> 01:11:13,197
There's a man
who can help us.

831
01:11:13,049 --> 01:11:17,201
Please,
we don't have much time.

832
01:11:32,068 --> 01:11:36,220
[Laughter]

833
01:11:46,082 --> 01:11:49,233
[Laughter Continues]

834
01:11:49,085 --> 01:11:53,237
- Unhh!
- [ Laughing ]

835
01:11:54,090 --> 01:11:58,242
- [ Both Grunting ]
- [ Giggling ]

836
01:12:07,103 --> 01:12:11,255
-[ Sobbing ]
-Mommy's busy right now, sweetheart.

837
01:12:15,111 --> 01:12:19,263
Why don't we go have a...
little talk.

838
01:12:19,115 --> 01:12:23,267
Just you and me.

839
01:12:23,119 --> 01:12:27,271
Think it's time
for another lesson.

840
01:12:29,125 --> 01:12:32,276
I assure you, Father Grissom
understands what you're up against.

841
01:12:32,128 --> 01:12:36,280
He was a Jesuit priest, a scholar
who was censured by the Vatican.

842
01:12:37,133 --> 01:12:41,285
The Devil's greatest
achievement...

843
01:12:41,137 --> 01:12:44,288
is that people don't
believe he exists.

844
01:12:44,140 --> 01:12:48,292
Nowadays the concept of evil
is politically incorrect.

845
01:12:49,145 --> 01:12:53,297
Then how could someone actually
recruit people to worship the Devil?

846
01:12:53,149 --> 01:12:56,300
Only a secret inner circle
practice traditional Satanism.

847
01:12:56,152 --> 01:12:59,303
But Eric Stark
and other groups like his...

848
01:12:59,155 --> 01:13:02,306
are spreading
a powerful message--

849
01:13:02,158 --> 01:13:06,310
God does not
really exist.

850
01:13:07,163 --> 01:13:11,315
Therefore, we can all
make up our own rules.

851
01:13:11,167 --> 01:13:15,319
Come with me.
I've got something to show you.

852
01:13:21,177 --> 01:13:24,328
These visions
that you've seen...

853
01:13:24,180 --> 01:13:28,332
have all been seen by others
throughout the centuries.

854
01:13:28,184 --> 01:13:30,334
Accounts of demonic attack
are common...

855
01:13:30,186 --> 01:13:32,336
in all cultures and religions.

856
01:13:32,188 --> 01:13:36,340
There, you see?

857
01:13:36,192 --> 01:13:38,342
There's a spiritual battle
going on in this world.

858
01:13:38,194 --> 01:13:42,346
We're all part of it
every day of our lives.

859
01:13:42,198 --> 01:13:44,348
- [ Sighs ]
- From what Sister Rosa has told me,

860
01:13:44,200 --> 01:13:48,352
I believe that Cody will be
an important part of this battle.

861
01:13:49,205 --> 01:13:53,357
I have seen the glory of God in
her, Maggie. I know you have too.

862
01:13:53,209 --> 01:13:57,361
What will
Eric do with her?

863
01:14:02,218 --> 01:14:04,368
''All these things
will I give thee,

864
01:14:04,220 --> 01:14:08,372
if thou wilt fall down
and worship me.''

865
01:14:10,226 --> 01:14:14,378
Satan's
temptation of Christ.

866
01:14:15,231 --> 01:14:18,382
He'll try to turn her
to his side, Maggie.

867
01:14:18,234 --> 01:14:21,385
- If he can't, he'll destroy her.
- What do I do?

868
01:14:21,237 --> 01:14:24,388
Get her back
whatever way you can.

869
01:14:24,240 --> 01:14:27,391
- I-I can't go back to Eric's place.
- Does she never leave?

870
01:14:27,243 --> 01:14:30,394
They're taking her
to the dentist tomorrow.

871
01:14:30,246 --> 01:14:33,397
Then, that's our chance!
John will go with you.

872
01:14:33,249 --> 01:14:36,400
I've helped families get their kids
out of New Dawn before.

873
01:14:36,252 --> 01:14:39,403
We won't make a move unless
we're sure she won't be hurt.

874
01:14:39,255 --> 01:14:41,405
These are directions
to our convent in Vermont.

875
01:14:41,257 --> 01:14:43,407
I'll be waiting
for you.

876
01:14:43,259 --> 01:14:46,410
- I don't know if I can do this.
- Yes, you can, Maggie.

877
01:14:46,262 --> 01:14:50,414
There is hope.
You must believe that.

878
01:14:51,267 --> 01:14:53,417
Not just for Cody.

879
01:14:53,269 --> 01:14:57,421
All of us are chosen
by God,

880
01:14:57,273 --> 01:15:01,425
and all of us can stand against
the darkness in His light.

881
01:15:09,285 --> 01:15:12,436
I never brought any of the other
children up here, Cody.

882
01:15:12,288 --> 01:15:16,440
Just you.

883
01:15:16,292 --> 01:15:20,444
- You know why?
- No.

884
01:15:20,296 --> 01:15:24,448
'Cause I'm your father
now, Cody.

885
01:15:24,300 --> 01:15:26,450
You never had
a father before, did you?

886
01:15:26,302 --> 01:15:29,453
No.

887
01:15:29,305 --> 01:15:33,457
Look.

888
01:15:33,309 --> 01:15:36,460
Pretty, isn't it?

889
01:15:36,312 --> 01:15:38,462
All this,

890
01:15:38,314 --> 01:15:41,465
as far
as the eye can see,

891
01:15:41,317 --> 01:15:45,469
is just a small part
of what can be yours, Cody,

892
01:15:45,321 --> 01:15:47,471
if you're
a good daughter...

893
01:15:47,323 --> 01:15:49,473
and you do
what I say.

894
01:15:49,325 --> 01:15:50,474
and you do
what I say.

895
01:15:50,326 --> 01:15:54,478
But you have
to choose...

896
01:15:54,330 --> 01:15:58,482
soon.

897
01:15:58,334 --> 01:16:02,486
This only works if it comes
from your heart.

898
01:16:03,339 --> 01:16:07,491
What does God offer
that compares?

899
01:16:08,344 --> 01:16:11,495
Does He even exist?

900
01:16:11,347 --> 01:16:14,498
Maybe God's
just a nice idea--

901
01:16:14,350 --> 01:16:17,501
like the Easter bunny.

902
01:16:17,353 --> 01:16:20,504
He's not real...

903
01:16:20,356 --> 01:16:24,508
is He?

904
01:16:25,361 --> 01:16:29,513
I know how
you can tell.

905
01:16:32,368 --> 01:16:36,520
[ Gasps ]

906
01:16:37,373 --> 01:16:41,525
In the Bible,
my lord says,

907
01:16:41,377 --> 01:16:44,528
''If thou be the child of God,
cast thee down from hence.

908
01:16:44,380 --> 01:16:48,532
''For He shall give His angels
charge over thee to keep thee...

909
01:16:48,384 --> 01:16:52,536
and in their hands
they shall bear thee up.''

910
01:16:52,388 --> 01:16:54,538
Jump, Cody.

911
01:16:54,390 --> 01:16:57,541
Jump.

912
01:16:57,393 --> 01:17:00,544
If you believe
in God, jump.

913
01:17:00,396 --> 01:17:03,547
If not,
you come to me.

914
01:17:03,399 --> 01:17:07,551
What do you believe in, Cody?
My hand?

915
01:17:07,403 --> 01:17:09,553
Huh? It's here.
You can see it.

916
01:17:09,405 --> 01:17:13,557
Satan rules it,
and it will protect you always.

917
01:17:13,409 --> 01:17:17,561
Or His hand?
ls it there?

918
01:17:17,413 --> 01:17:21,565
Huh?
Or isn't it?

919
01:17:21,417 --> 01:17:25,569
Will He catch
you or not?

920
01:17:25,421 --> 01:17:28,572
- If you believe, Cody,
- [Panting]

921
01:17:28,424 --> 01:17:32,576
jump!

922
01:17:36,432 --> 01:17:40,584
-Jump!
- [ Gasps ]

923
01:17:55,451 --> 01:17:59,603
After you.

924
01:18:02,458 --> 01:18:06,610
Ahh!

925
01:18:10,466 --> 01:18:14,618
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
I'm sorry, darling.

926
01:18:15,471 --> 01:18:18,622
Come on.

927
01:18:18,474 --> 01:18:22,626
Let's get you
back inside.

928
01:18:23,479 --> 01:18:26,630
Bugatti, homicide.

929
01:18:26,482 --> 01:18:28,632
- Agent Travis.
- Travis-- I heard of you.

930
01:18:28,484 --> 01:18:32,636
None of your voodoo stuff here.
Just some bum got torched.

931
01:18:34,490 --> 01:18:37,641
Hey, Frank.
How are you doing?

932
01:18:37,493 --> 01:18:41,645
[Chattering, Indistinct]

933
01:18:57,513 --> 01:19:00,664
It's a Druid rune spell.

934
01:19:00,516 --> 01:19:03,667
Straight out of the 16th century.

935
01:19:03,519 --> 01:19:05,669
Think we know
how it started.

936
01:19:05,521 --> 01:19:08,672
How long will it take your forensics
lab to get prints off of that?

937
01:19:08,524 --> 01:19:11,675
Mm, call in a favor,
a couple of hours, maybe.

938
01:19:11,527 --> 01:19:13,677
We're out of time on this, Frank.
It's Easter eve.

939
01:19:13,529 --> 01:19:16,680
We have Stark's prints on file from
a drug bust in '82. If they match--

940
01:19:16,532 --> 01:19:18,682
If they match,
I'll get you a warrant...

941
01:19:18,534 --> 01:19:22,686
on this Devil-lovin' bastard
before lunch.

942
01:19:52,568 --> 01:19:56,720
Hold it. There they are.

943
01:20:17,593 --> 01:20:21,745
[Woman]
No, it's fine. Sure.

944
01:20:21,597 --> 01:20:24,748
Yeah, tomorrow
at 5:00, okay?

945
01:20:24,600 --> 01:20:26,750
Yeah. No, I'm sure
we can fit you in.

946
01:20:26,602 --> 01:20:30,754
Okay? Have a good afternoon.
Bye.

947
01:20:32,608 --> 01:20:36,760
- Yes?
- Thank you.

948
01:20:37,613 --> 01:20:41,765
[Drill Whirring]

949
01:20:42,618 --> 01:20:46,770
[Child Whimpering]

950
01:20:51,627 --> 01:20:55,779
- Mim!
- [Dentist] We're just about done.

951
01:20:55,631 --> 01:20:58,782
Tell Eric I'll have the new
dental records ready by tonight.

952
01:20:58,634 --> 01:21:00,784
Thank you, Doctor.
That's a relief.

953
01:21:00,636 --> 01:21:04,788
Wait a minute!

954
01:21:08,644 --> 01:21:12,796
- [Door Opening]
- Maggie, I was getting worried.

955
01:21:13,649 --> 01:21:17,801
[ Groans ]

956
01:21:31,667 --> 01:21:35,819
Ohh!

957
01:21:37,673 --> 01:21:39,823
Wait!

958
01:21:39,675 --> 01:21:43,827
[ Tires Screeching,
Horns Blaring ]

959
01:21:43,679 --> 01:21:47,831
- Stop that woman!
- [ Horn Honking ]

960
01:21:49,685 --> 01:21:53,837
[ Tires Screeching ]

961
01:21:54,690 --> 01:21:58,842
- Oh.
- [ Screams ]

962
01:21:59,695 --> 01:22:02,846
[ Tires Screeching ]

963
01:22:02,698 --> 01:22:06,850
Run, Cody! Run!

964
01:22:10,706 --> 01:22:14,858
After you.

965
01:22:14,710 --> 01:22:18,862
Thank you.

966
01:22:23,719 --> 01:22:25,869
- [ Grunts ]
- [ Gasps ]

967
01:22:25,721 --> 01:22:29,873
[ Shrieking, Growling ]

968
01:22:47,743 --> 01:22:49,893
Eric Stark,
this is the police!

969
01:22:49,745 --> 01:22:53,897
We have a warrant
to search the premises!

970
01:22:53,749 --> 01:22:57,901
[Pounding]

971
01:23:04,760 --> 01:23:08,912
[ Beeping ]

972
01:23:08,764 --> 01:23:10,914
Where we going, Mim?

973
01:23:10,766 --> 01:23:14,918
Vermont, to see Sister Rosa.
She has some friends there.

974
01:23:15,771 --> 01:23:19,923
- Kids? Like at school?
- We'll see.

975
01:23:20,776 --> 01:23:22,926
Looks like he blew town.

976
01:23:22,778 --> 01:23:23,927
We've gotta strip this place
down to the floorboards...

977
01:23:23,779 --> 01:23:25,929
until we find a lead on him.

978
01:23:25,781 --> 01:23:27,931
The little girl's
only got a few hours left.

979
01:23:27,783 --> 01:23:28,932
- You got anything?
- Not yet.

980
01:23:28,784 --> 01:23:31,935
We have access,
but his files are encrypted.

981
01:23:31,787 --> 01:23:35,939
We need anything on property that
he owns, places he might be staying.

982
01:23:39,795 --> 01:23:42,946
Just a whole lot
of nothing.

983
01:23:42,798 --> 01:23:46,950
Mm-hmm.

984
01:23:49,805 --> 01:23:53,957
[ Scoffs ]
Not even dust.

985
01:23:54,810 --> 01:23:58,962
Paint's fresh.

986
01:24:06,822 --> 01:24:09,973
Does your forensics team
have an A.L.S.?

987
01:24:09,825 --> 01:24:13,977
- Yeah, they got all those toys.
- We're gonna need it.

988
01:24:34,850 --> 01:24:38,001
[Coins Dropping]

989
01:24:37,853 --> 01:24:40,003
[ Dialing ]

990
01:24:39,855 --> 01:24:44,007
[ Line Ringing ]

991
01:24:44,860 --> 01:24:49,012
- Oh, thank you.
- Buenos dias.

992
01:24:48,864 --> 01:24:52,015
- Hi.
- You're sick.

993
01:24:51,867 --> 01:24:55,018
Oh, I'm so sorry.

994
01:24:54,870 --> 01:24:59,022
Out of the mouths
of babes, huh?

995
01:25:27,903 --> 01:25:32,055
- [Tires Screeching]
- Go!

996
01:25:35,911 --> 01:25:40,063
- [ Horn Honking ]
- [ Brakes Squealing ]

997
01:25:40,916 --> 01:25:45,068
[ Tires Screeching ]

998
01:25:54,930 --> 01:25:59,082
- [ Horn Honking ]
- [ Tires Screeching ]

999
01:26:28,964 --> 01:26:32,115
[Honking Horn]

1000
01:26:31,967 --> 01:26:36,119
- [ Tires Screeching ]
- [ Siren Wailing ]

1001
01:26:40,976 --> 01:26:43,126
- What the hell are you doing?
- Officer, you don't understand.

1002
01:26:42,978 --> 01:26:45,128
- Give me your keys, now!
- They're trying to kill us.

1003
01:26:44,980 --> 01:26:49,132
- License and registration.
- [ Vehicle Approaching]

1004
01:26:53,989 --> 01:26:57,140
[ Tires Screeching ]

1005
01:26:56,992 --> 01:27:00,143
We've got
to get out of here!

1006
01:26:59,995 --> 01:27:03,146
Run!
Run, baby, run!

1007
01:27:02,998 --> 01:27:07,150
Go! Go!

1008
01:27:10,005 --> 01:27:14,157
[ Screams ]

1009
01:27:21,016 --> 01:27:24,167
Looks like your boy's got serious
money stashed in the Caymans.

1010
01:27:24,019 --> 01:27:26,169
The I.R.S. might be able
to make a case.

1011
01:27:26,021 --> 01:27:28,171
What about property?

1012
01:27:28,023 --> 01:27:30,173
He owns some kind of country estate
north of the city.

1013
01:27:30,025 --> 01:27:32,175
- I need an address on that.
- Workin' on it.

1014
01:27:32,027 --> 01:27:36,179
- Okay.
- We're all set.

1015
01:27:41,036 --> 01:27:45,188
Lights, please.

1016
01:27:51,046 --> 01:27:55,198
Try over here.

1017
01:27:57,052 --> 01:27:59,202
Oh, my God.

1018
01:27:59,054 --> 01:28:02,205
Think your guys can pull
DNA off of that?

1019
01:28:02,057 --> 01:28:04,207
[Technician]
Yes, sir.

1020
01:28:04,059 --> 01:28:07,210
Need to run a match
against the kids.

1021
01:28:07,062 --> 01:28:10,213
Yeah. Yeah.
Lights, please.

1022
01:28:10,065 --> 01:28:13,216
- [Cell Phone Ringing]
- How long is it gonna take you...

1023
01:28:13,068 --> 01:28:16,219
- to get those crates analyzed?
- Hello.

1024
01:28:16,071 --> 01:28:19,222
Agent Travis, it's Maggie.
They've got Cody.

1025
01:28:19,074 --> 01:28:22,225
- Where are you?
- I'm at a diner on Route 17...

1026
01:28:22,077 --> 01:28:26,229
- about 30 miles south of Albany
- Do not move.

1027
01:28:26,081 --> 01:28:29,232
Don't talk to anyone. I'll be there
as soon as I can, okay?

1028
01:28:29,084 --> 01:28:32,235
- Okay. [ Hangs Up ]
- Agent Travis?

1029
01:28:32,087 --> 01:28:35,238
Got a location on that estate.
It's just off 87--

1030
01:28:35,090 --> 01:28:37,240
Let me guess.
Just outside of Albany.

1031
01:28:37,092 --> 01:28:39,242
Right.

1032
01:28:39,094 --> 01:28:41,244
It'll take a couple of hours to get
there. I'll call the State Troopers.

1033
01:28:41,096 --> 01:28:43,246
I'll catch a lift from Air Support,
and I'll meet you there.

1034
01:28:43,098 --> 01:28:46,249
- I'm gonna need local backup.
- You got it.

1035
01:28:46,101 --> 01:28:50,253
[ Siren Blares ]

1036
01:29:00,115 --> 01:29:03,266
- Maggie! Are you all right?
- Yes.

1037
01:29:03,118 --> 01:29:05,268
Stark's on the move.

1038
01:29:05,120 --> 01:29:07,270
Our best guess
is that he took Cody...

1039
01:29:07,122 --> 01:29:10,273
to an old estate he owns
just north of here.

1040
01:29:10,125 --> 01:29:12,275
We're gonna get her back,
though. I promise you that.

1041
01:29:12,127 --> 01:29:13,276
- You Travis?
- Yeah, that's right.

1042
01:29:13,128 --> 01:29:15,278
The place is about a half
an hour away from here.

1043
01:29:15,130 --> 01:29:17,280
Local police have already
done some reconnaissance.

1044
01:29:17,132 --> 01:29:19,282
- How's it look?
- The entrance is guarded.

1045
01:29:19,134 --> 01:29:20,283
Oh, that's no good.

1046
01:29:20,135 --> 01:29:23,286
The element of surprise is the key
thing. They might hurt the girl.

1047
01:29:23,138 --> 01:29:25,288
Well, there used to be a dirt road
about two miles up the interstate.

1048
01:29:25,140 --> 01:29:27,290
It's probably overgrown.
Could get us on the grounds.

1049
01:29:27,142 --> 01:29:31,294
All right, we'll rendezvous there.
No flashers. No sirens.

1050
01:29:32,147 --> 01:29:36,299
No one goes in that property
until my command!

1051
01:29:44,159 --> 01:29:48,311
Ah! The prodigal daughter
returns!

1052
01:29:48,163 --> 01:29:52,315
Just in time
for her last supper.

1053
01:29:53,168 --> 01:29:57,320
It's Eastereve,
sweetheart.

1054
01:29:57,172 --> 01:30:01,324
You only have
a few hours left.

1055
01:30:01,176 --> 01:30:05,328
Tonight you can be
reborn through my lord,

1056
01:30:05,180 --> 01:30:09,332
or die for yours.

1057
01:30:09,184 --> 01:30:11,334
You're alone, Cody.

1058
01:30:13,188 --> 01:30:15,338
And through me...

1059
01:30:15,190 --> 01:30:19,342
him.

1060
01:30:20,195 --> 01:30:24,347
Now, this is the last time
I'm going to ask you.

1061
01:30:25,200 --> 01:30:29,352
Join us, Cody.

1062
01:30:30,205 --> 01:30:32,355
Join us...

1063
01:30:32,207 --> 01:30:36,359
if you want to live.

1064
01:30:37,212 --> 01:30:41,364
Cody, do what he says.

1065
01:30:42,217 --> 01:30:46,369
Please.

1066
01:31:10,245 --> 01:31:14,397
Is that it?

1067
01:31:14,249 --> 01:31:18,401
Is that all you can do?

1068
01:31:20,255 --> 01:31:22,405
Dahnia, I don't think
Cody's hungry.

1069
01:31:22,257 --> 01:31:26,409
Why don't you prepare the Light
of the World for her big night.

1070
01:31:28,263 --> 01:31:32,415
- Has she called?
- Still nothing.

1071
01:31:32,267 --> 01:31:36,419
Mother Superior is ready
to lock up for the night.

1072
01:31:37,272 --> 01:31:39,422
They should've
been here hours ago.

1073
01:31:39,274 --> 01:31:40,423
What do you want me to do?

1074
01:31:40,275 --> 01:31:43,426
Tell everyone to meet me
in the chapel.

1075
01:31:43,278 --> 01:31:45,428
These people are
under attack, Sister.

1076
01:31:45,280 --> 01:31:49,432
They need our prayers.

1077
01:32:08,303 --> 01:32:10,453
[Travis]
That must be it.

1078
01:32:10,305 --> 01:32:12,455
I want you to stay
in the car.

1079
01:32:12,307 --> 01:32:15,458
I need to be there
for Cody.

1080
01:32:15,310 --> 01:32:19,462
I'm serious, Maggie.

1081
01:32:23,318 --> 01:32:26,469
Where's that backup?

1082
01:32:26,321 --> 01:32:30,473
They were
right behind us.

1083
01:32:30,325 --> 01:32:33,476
They've got to be
right back there somewhere.

1084
01:32:33,328 --> 01:32:37,480
You wait for them at the turn off.
We'll stay here.

1085
01:32:55,350 --> 01:32:58,501
You look so beautiful,
little one.

1086
01:32:58,353 --> 01:33:00,503
[ Snaps Fingers ]

1087
01:33:00,355 --> 01:33:04,507
Tonight is a very
special night.

1088
01:33:05,360 --> 01:33:07,510
Tonight...

1089
01:33:07,362 --> 01:33:11,514
you must make your mommy
and new daddy...

1090
01:33:11,366 --> 01:33:15,518
proud.

1091
01:33:35,390 --> 01:33:38,541
[ Grunts ]

1092
01:33:38,393 --> 01:33:40,543
[ Whispering ]
Thanks for waiting.

1093
01:33:40,395 --> 01:33:43,546
Lights are on
upstairs.

1094
01:33:43,398 --> 01:33:47,550
Okay.

1095
01:33:49,404 --> 01:33:53,556
Let me check.

1096
01:34:00,415 --> 01:34:04,567
- Maggie!
- [ Grunts ]

1097
01:34:05,420 --> 01:34:09,572
[ Grunts ]

1098
01:34:10,425 --> 01:34:12,575
[ Yelling, Grunting ]

1099
01:34:12,427 --> 01:34:16,579
[ Groans ]

1100
01:34:18,433 --> 01:34:22,585
- [ Groaning ]
- Come on! She's getting away!

1101
01:34:23,438 --> 01:34:27,590
[ Panting ]

1102
01:34:53,468 --> 01:34:57,620
Hey--

1103
01:34:57,472 --> 01:35:01,624
[Clamoring]

1104
01:35:19,494 --> 01:35:22,645
You bastard!

1105
01:35:22,497 --> 01:35:25,648
It's customary
for guests to kneel.

1106
01:35:25,500 --> 01:35:29,652
[Men Chanting]

1107
01:35:34,509 --> 01:35:38,661
- Cody!
- [ Chanting Continues ]

1108
01:35:38,513 --> 01:35:42,665
[Rustling]

1109
01:36:02,537 --> 01:36:05,688
[ Snarling ]

1110
01:36:05,540 --> 01:36:08,691
For the girl Cody,
the innocent,

1111
01:36:08,543 --> 01:36:12,695
that she may one day
stand against the dragon,

1112
01:36:12,547 --> 01:36:15,698
-we pray to the Lord.
-[ Together ] Lord, hear our prayer.

1113
01:36:15,550 --> 01:36:18,701
For Maggie O'Connor, that she
will have faith in you, Lord,

1114
01:36:18,553 --> 01:36:21,704
-grant her strength.
-[ Together ] Lord, hear our prayer.

1115
01:36:21,556 --> 01:36:23,706
Send your angels
to protect them, Father.

1116
01:36:23,558 --> 01:36:24,707
[Bell Tolling]

1117
01:36:24,559 --> 01:36:28,711
Send your angels to stand against
the forces of darkness...

1118
01:36:28,563 --> 01:36:30,713
that would do them harm.

1119
01:36:30,565 --> 01:36:33,716
- We pray to the Lord.
- Lord, hear our prayer.

1120
01:36:33,568 --> 01:36:36,719
This is it, Cody.

1121
01:36:36,571 --> 01:36:40,723
I know you like angels,
don't you?

1122
01:36:40,575 --> 01:36:43,726
Well, Satan was an angel too--

1123
01:36:43,578 --> 01:36:46,729
the most beautiful angel
of them all.

1124
01:36:46,581 --> 01:36:49,732
So beautiful...

1125
01:36:49,584 --> 01:36:53,736
that God gave him
dominion over the earth.

1126
01:36:57,592 --> 01:37:01,744
No!
[ Gasps ]

1127
01:37:03,598 --> 01:37:05,748
All you have to do...

1128
01:37:05,600 --> 01:37:09,752
is cry out to him.

1129
01:37:10,605 --> 01:37:12,755
Ask him for mercy.

1130
01:37:12,607 --> 01:37:16,759
Callhis name.

1131
01:37:18,613 --> 01:37:22,765
Say his name!

1132
01:37:26,621 --> 01:37:30,773
[ Exhales Sharply ]

1133
01:37:31,626 --> 01:37:35,778
- [ Cocks Gun ]
- Choose, Cody.

1134
01:37:35,630 --> 01:37:38,781
Choose Satan as your god,
or your beloved Mim dies.

1135
01:37:38,633 --> 01:37:41,784
- No!
- Don't, Cody. Don't.

1136
01:37:41,636 --> 01:37:45,788
Close your eyes.
We're faraway from here.

1137
01:37:46,641 --> 01:37:47,790
We're together.

1138
01:37:47,642 --> 01:37:49,792
- We'll always be together.
- What's your choice?

1139
01:37:49,644 --> 01:37:51,794
What's
your choice, Cody?

1140
01:37:51,646 --> 01:37:55,798
Say it!

1141
01:37:56,651 --> 01:38:00,803
- Police! Open up!
- [ Crowd Clamoring ]

1142
01:38:00,655 --> 01:38:04,807
[Glass Breaking]

1143
01:38:08,663 --> 01:38:11,814
Kill the girl!
Shoot her!

1144
01:38:11,666 --> 01:38:15,818
[ Groans ]

1145
01:38:18,673 --> 01:38:22,825
- [ Grunts ]
- Mim!

1146
01:38:22,677 --> 01:38:24,827
[ Gunshot ]

1147
01:38:24,679 --> 01:38:28,831
No!

1148
01:38:30,685 --> 01:38:33,836
- [ Crying ]
- [ Grunting ]

1149
01:38:33,688 --> 01:38:37,840
[ Groans ]

1150
01:38:42,697 --> 01:38:46,849
[ Exhales Slowly ]

1151
01:39:25,740 --> 01:39:29,892
[ Gasps ]

1152
01:39:43,758 --> 01:39:47,910
I deliver you
unto... him.

1153
01:40:03,778 --> 01:40:07,930
Drop!

1154
01:40:32,807 --> 01:40:35,958
- Maggie!
- [Creaking, Rumbling]

1155
01:40:35,810 --> 01:40:39,962
- Maggie!
- [Creaking Continues]

1156
01:40:40,815 --> 01:40:44,967
[ Yelling ]

1157
01:40:44,819 --> 01:40:48,971
[ Yells ]

1158
01:40:50,825 --> 01:40:52,975
Are you hurt?

1159
01:40:52,827 --> 01:40:56,979
Keep your head down!

1160
01:40:58,833 --> 01:41:02,985
Jenna!

1161
01:41:14,849 --> 01:41:19,001
Come on, Maggie!

1162
01:41:30,865 --> 01:41:35,017
Was anybody else
in there?

1163
01:41:39,874 --> 01:41:44,026
[ Sobs ]

1164
01:41:49,884 --> 01:41:52,034
So, are you going back
to work at the hospital?

1165
01:41:51,886 --> 01:41:56,038
- If they'll have me.
- How's Jenna doin' in rehab?

1166
01:41:56,891 --> 01:41:59,041
Fine, so far.

1167
01:41:58,893 --> 01:42:03,045
She asked me
to adopt Cody.

1168
01:42:02,897 --> 01:42:07,049
No one will ever take
her away from me again.

1169
01:42:08,903 --> 01:42:12,054
Come on. We're gonna be
late for the church bells.

1170
01:42:11,906 --> 01:42:16,058
We're
right on time.

1171
01:42:18,913 --> 01:42:23,065
You ready?
Ten, nine, eight,

1172
01:42:22,917 --> 01:42:27,069
seven, six, five,

1173
01:42:26,921 --> 01:42:30,072
four, three,

1174
01:42:29,924 --> 01:42:32,074
two, one.

1175
01:42:31,926 --> 01:42:36,078
[ Bells Chiming ]

1176
01:42:48,943 --> 01:42:53,095
[Knife Clatters]

1177
01:42:53,948 --> 01:42:56,098
Are you all right?

1178
01:42:55,950 --> 01:43:00,102
It's all right now.

1179
01:43:01,956 --> 01:43:06,108
[ Children Shouting,
Laughing ]

